   MIMULUS-GUTTATUS (SCROPHULARIACEAE)},
Journal = {AMERICAN JOURNAL OF BOTANY},
Year = {1990},
Volume = {77},
Number = {11},
Pages = {1505-1507},
Month = {NOV},
Abstract = {Corollas of Mimulus guttatus are shed 1-9 days post-anthesis, and
   autofertility of often high. The possibility that corolla shedding
   causes self-pollination in the absence of pollinators was examined. In
   one experimental population 82\% of seed produced under conditions of
   pollinator exclusion were due to corolla abscission. Corolla abscission,
   in the absence of pollinators, is a mechanism of delayed
   self-fertilization in this taxon.},
