Month = {JAN-MAR},
Abstract = {Notes on oil sources for the bee genus Caenonomada (Hymenoptera, Apidae,
   Tapinotaspidini). It is reported for the first time oil collecting by
   bees of the genus Caenonomada on flowers of Plantaginaceae. Females of
   Caenonomada unicalcarata were observed collecting oil on flowers of
   Angelonia cornigera. and males and females of Caenonomada bruneri and C.
   aff. unicalcarata were observed on flowers of Angelonia and Monopera
   (Plantaginaceae). The record of Caenonomada on Plantaginaceae suggests
   the use of trichomatic oil glands as a primitive condition in the tribe
   Tapinotaspidini.},
